intention: Clinical Focus: Transfusion of Blood or Blood Products.; Data Element Scope: Transfusion of blood or certain blood products that exposes a person to transmission of and infection with bloodborn viruses.; Inclusion Criteria: Procedures related to transfusion, push transfusion or exchange transfusion of blood or blood components in newborn, children and adults. intention: Clinical Focus: This value set identifies patients with a diagnosis of chronic obstructive pulmonary disorder (COPD).; Data Element Scope: This value set was intended to map to the QDM data type of diagnosis, but has the potential to be used in additional ways.; Inclusion Criteria: This value set includes acute COPD exacerbations, and end stage COPD. limitations: Exclusion Criteria: This value set excludes concurrent infections. It also excludes diagnoses of bronchitis, bronchiolitis, and emphysema.

comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: Clinical Focus: Evidence of a hematopoietic stem cell transplant (HSCT) (i.e., bone marrow transplant) in the patient record.; Data Element Scope: Evidence that a HSCT has been performed on the patient. Since SNOMED CT does not provide disorder codes for HSCT, this VS only consists of "disorder" codes that represent complications of HSCT.; Inclusion Criteria: SNOMED CT disorder codes that represent complications of HSCTs (regardless of the type of bone marrow/stem cell transplant). Active and inactive codes since inactive codes are not always updated in a patient record.
limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Complications from other types of transplants, other types of SNOMED codes (e.g., "finding", "situation"). Chronic and Genital Graft vs. Host Disease.
provenance: Steward: MITRE; OID: 2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1032.220; dih_id: 1000000289; Code System(s): SNOMEDCT; Definition Type: Extensional; Definition Version: Latest; Accessed: 2022-04-05 18:52:18

limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that represent a diagnosis of juvenile chronic polyarthritis, chronic post rheumatic arthropathy, or inflammatory polyarthropathy.
